    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of the species Betula papyrifera, native to northern and central North America. Almost white in color, it is used for flooring, furniture, canoes, and objects such as spools, bobbins, dowels, and crates.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
